ADDITIONAL PERMISSIONS UNDER GNU AGPL v3 SECTION 7 (Plugin Exception)

1. Plugin Exception
As a special exception to the GNU Affero General Public License version 3 ("AGPL v3"), the copyright holders of Ubichill grant you permission to link, load, or combine the Ubichill core application with independent plugins. You may license and distribute such independent plugins under terms of your choice (including closed-source, proprietary, or commercial licenses), provided that the plugin meets the conditions of "Plugin Independence" defined in Section 2. The Ubichill core application itself remains fully subject to the AGPL v3.

2. Plugin Independence
To qualify for this exception, a plugin must be considered an "independent plugin" by satisfying all of the following criteria:
a) It must be distributed independently of the Ubichill core.
b) It must interact with the Ubichill core solely through the documented public Plugin API or stable public extension interfaces.
c) It must not require modifications to the Ubichill core source code to function (e.g., core modification mods are not covered by this exception).

3. No Warranty for Plugins
TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY APPLICABLE LAW, THE COPYRIGHT HOLDERS DISCLAIM ALL WARRANTIES REGARDING THIRD-PARTY PLUGINS. Ubichill makes no warranty regarding the security, functionality, or confidentiality (including protection of plugin source code) of dynamically loaded plugins. Any user or server operator who loads, links, or executes a third-party plugin does so entirely at their own risk. The copyright holders shall not be liable for any damages, data loss, or security breaches resulting from the use of such plugins.

